---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Basics of Prompting">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>‚úçÔ∏è Basics of Prompting</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">
            How to talk to an AI effectively ‚Äî from simple instructions to
            powerful techniques
        </p>
        <div class="doc-link">
            <a
                href="https://www.promptingguide.ai/introduction/basics"
                target="_blank">üìÑ View Original Docs ‚Äî promptingguide.ai</a
            >
        </div>

        <!-- Core idea -->
        <div class="section-title">üí° The Core Idea</div>
        <div class="concept-card">
            <h3>What is a Prompt?</h3>
            <p>
                A prompt is simply what you <strong style="color:#e2e8f0;"
                    >type to the AI</strong
                > to get a response. It can be a question, an instruction, or even
                just an incomplete sentence. The better your prompt, the better the
                answer.
            </p>
            <p class="hint">
                üß† Think of it like giving instructions to a new employee ‚Äî
                vague instructions = vague results. Clear instructions = great
                results.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Bad vs Good comparison -->
        <div class="section-title">‚ö° Vague Prompt vs. Clear Prompt</div>
        <div class="comparison">
            <div class="prompt-box">
                <span class="label label-bad">üòï Vague Prompt</span>
                <div class="prompt-text">The sky is</div>
                <div class="output-text">Output: <span>blue.</span></div>
                <div class="verdict bad">
                    ‚ùå Too short ‚Äî AI just completes the sentence randomly
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="prompt-box">
                <span class="label label-good">‚úÖ Clear Prompt</span>
                <div class="prompt-text">Complete the sentence: The sky is</div>
                <div class="output-text">
                    Output: <span>blue during the day and dark at night.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="verdict good">
                    ‚úÖ Better! AI now knows exactly what to do
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Prompt Roles -->
        <div class="section-title">üé≠ The 3 Roles in a Prompt</div>
        <p style="font-size:0.85rem; color:#94a3b8; margin-bottom:1rem;">
            When using chat models (like GPT-4 or Claude), prompts can have 3
            roles. Most of the time you only use "User".
        </p>
        <div class="roles">
            <div class="role-card system">
                <div class="role-icon">‚öôÔ∏è</div>
                <div class="role-name">System</div>
                <p>
                    Sets the AI's overall behavior and personality before the
                    conversation starts
                </p>
                <span class="required">Optional</span>
            </div>
            <div class="role-card user">
                <div class="role-icon">üßë</div>
                <div class="role-name">User</div>
                <p>
                    Your message ‚Äî the question or instruction you send to the
                    AI
                </p>
                <span class="required">Always Used</span>
            </div>
            <div class="role-card assistant">
                <div class="role-icon">ü§ñ</div>
                <div class="role-name">Assistant</div>
                <p>
                    The AI's reply. Can also be pre-filled to show the AI
                    examples of the style you want
                </p>
                <span class="required">Optional</span>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Shot Types -->
        <div class="section-title">
            üéØ Prompting Techniques ‚Äî Zero-shot vs Few-shot
        </div>
        <p style="font-size:0.85rem; color:#94a3b8; margin-bottom:1rem;">
            Click each tab to see how it works with a real example:
        </p>
        <div class="shot-tabs">
            <div class="shot-tab active" onclick="showShot(event, 'zero')">
                Zero-shot
            </div>
            <div class="shot-tab" onclick="showShot(event, 'few')">
                Few-shot
            </div>
            <div class="shot-tab" onclick="showShot(event, 'qa')">
                Q&A Format
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="shot-content active" id="shot-zero">
            <p class="desc">
                <strong style="color:#e2e8f0;">Zero-shot</strong> means you give the
                AI NO examples ‚Äî just ask directly. Works great for simple tasks with
                modern models.
            </p>
            <p class="hint">
                üß† Like asking a new employee to do something with zero training
                ‚Äî works if they're smart enough!
            </p>
            <div class="code-block">
                <span class="prompt-label">PROMPT:</span>
                What is prompt engineering?

                <span class="output-label">OUTPUT:</span>
                Prompt engineering is the practice of designing and refining inputs
                to AI models to get better, more accurate responses...
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="shot-content" id="shot-few">
            <p class="desc">
                <strong style="color:#e2e8f0;">Few-shot</strong> means you give the
                AI 2‚Äì3 examples first, then ask your question. The AI learns the pattern
                from your examples and follows it.
            </p>
            <p class="hint">
                üß† Like showing an employee 3 examples of how you want a task
                done, then asking them to do it themselves.
            </p>
            <div class="code-block">
                <span class="prompt-label">PROMPT (with examples):</span>
                This is awesome! <span class="comment">// Positive</span>
                This is bad! <span class="comment">// Negative</span>
                Wow, great movie! <span class="comment">// Positive</span>
                What a horrible show! <span class="comment">// ???</span>

                <span class="output-label">OUTPUT:</span>
                Negative
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="shot-content" id="shot-qa">
            <p class="desc">
                <strong style="color:#e2e8f0;">Q&A Format</strong> is a simple structure
                where you explicitly write "Q:" before your question and "A:" to signal
                where the answer should go. Helps the AI understand it's a question-answer
                task.
            </p>
            <p class="hint">
                üß† Like filling in a form ‚Äî the labels make the structure
                crystal clear.
            </p>
            <div class="code-block">
                <span class="prompt-label">PROMPT:</span>
                Q: What is the capital of Egypt? A:

                <span class="output-label">OUTPUT:</span>
                Cairo

                <span class="comment">// Multiple Q&A in one prompt:</span>
                Q: What is 2 + 2? A: 4 Q: What is the capital of France? A: Paris
                Q: What is the capital of Japan? A:
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Prompt quality checker -->
        <div class="try-it">
            <h3>üß™ Prompt Quality Checker</h3>
            <p>
                Type a prompt below and see how well-structured it is based on
                what we learned:
            </p>
            <textarea
                id="prompt-input"
                placeholder="Type your prompt here... e.g. 'What is AI?'"
                oninput="checkPrompt()"></textarea>
            <div class="score-display" id="score-display" style="display:none;">
                <div class="score-label">
                    <span>Clarity</span><span id="clarity-pct">0%</span>
                </div>
                <div class="score-bar">
                    <div
                        class="score-fill"
                        id="clarity-bar"
                        style="width:0%; background:#6366f1;"
                    >
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="score-label">
                    <span>Specificity</span><span id="specific-pct">0%</span>
                </div>
                <div class="score-bar">
                    <div
                        class="score-fill"
                        id="specific-bar"
                        style="width:0%; background:#059669;"
                    >
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="score-feedback" id="score-feedback"></div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tip-banner">
            <span style="font-size:1.4rem; flex-shrink:0;">üí°</span>
            <p>
                <strong>Key Takeaway:</strong> Prompt engineering is just about being
                <strong>clear and specific</strong> with the AI. Start simple (zero-shot),
                and if the answer isn't good enough, add examples (few-shot) or more
                context. The more information you give, the better the result.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>

<style>
